article.description: — Gibson Jimerson had 28 points as Saint Louis beat George Washington 80-67 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Jimerson leads Saint Louis past George Washington 80-67
article.linkText: Jimerson leads Saint Louis past George Washington 80-67
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- — Gibson Jimerson had 28 points as Saint Louis beat George Washington 80-67 on Wednesday night. Francis Okoro added 22 points for the Billikens. Okoro also had 11 rebounds. Yuri Collins had 11 points and 12 assists for Saint Louis (13-6, 4-2 Atlantic 10 Conference), which earned its fifth straight home victory. Fred Thatch Jr. added three blocks. James Bishop scored a career-high 30 points for the Colonials (6-12, 2-4). Joe Bamisile added 18 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
